DESCRIPTION: Provides a minimal example of a Playwright test in TypeScript that navigates to a web page and checks its title. Depends on the @playwright/test module. The 'test' function initializes a test block, while 'expect' is used for assertion. Parameter: 'page' (injected by Playwright) representing a browser page. Inputs: none directly (hardcoded URL). Output: Passes if the title matches /Example/, fails otherwise. Designed to be placed in a .spec.ts file within the tests directory.
SOURCE: https://github.com/copilotkit/copilotkit/blob/main/examples/e2e/README.md#2025-04-23_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { test, expect } from "@playwright/test";\n\ntest("basic test", async ({ page }) => {\n  await page.goto("https://example.com");\n  await expect(page).toHaveTitle(/Example/);\n});
```

